Description: Sherd of Etruscan bucchero pottery trefoil oinochoe; burnished; rim, neck and part of handle; trefoil mouth; grey ware; groove just below rim on outside; another three joining fragments which are separate.
Curator's comments: See also Johnston 1982, 38 and pl. 4a and Naso 2006, 190 with fig. 7.
Bibliographic references: Etruscan Bucchero / A Catalogue of Etruscan Bucchero in the British Museum (No. 236)
Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p.260, no.1)
Johnston 1978 / Pottery from Naukratis: An Exhibition on the Occasion of the 11th International Congress of Classical Archaeology (no. 22)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GQ.04)
